txt.en: 'We have guests!'
'Seems to me that that's none of your business. Is it, boys?'
'Ah, Captain Hebil. What are you doing on my turf?'
'Seems to me that that's none of your business. Is it, boys?'
'I ask you instead, Jajax, what this outsider is doing on your turf.'
'I ask you instead, Jajax, what this outsider is doing on your turf.'
Damkalb
'You wish us to leave this town we rightfully stole?'
'A bold request of a tavern full of Corsairs.'
'Whether you are brave or foolish, I know not.'
'But I will tell you straight why you are permitted to stand before me thus, making such requests.'
'I will tell you straight why you are permitted to stand before me thus.'
'You came here to take back this town, which is your right.'
'You came here to take back this town, which is your right.'
'You fought many of my men to do this, and defeated all who stood in your way.'
'You wish us to leave this town we rightfully stole?'
'I believe that you are a formidable foe...'
'A bold request to make of a tavern full of Corsairs.'
'...And I would have you stop attacking my men.'
'So I say to you: We will leave, if you vow not to raise your weapons against us again.'
'Whether you are brave or foolish, I know not.'
